narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: You get to read some amazing French literature in a laid-back atmosphere. If you don't mind listening more than you participate and analyzing the slightest turns of phrase and details, you'll enjoy the class.
It's a wonderful course. It's a small seminar, which gives you all the freedom to express your ideas that you want, and the books are very interesting and fun to read. Take this class if you can!
It is a course in which you read french novels in translation and analyze the literature. Think of it as a literature course but dealing only in french novels and involving some context of the times.
